r><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bees fly out to collect honey for the winter</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>adæm dʼalvars æmbyrd sty</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>народ окружает тебя</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the people are crowding</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>8 45</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cæmæn wæ æmbyrd kæny Qævdyn?</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зачем вас собирает Кавдын?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>why is Qavdyn convoking you?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>īwmæ næ rambyrd kæn, arfæjy ʒyrd!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>собери нас вместе, благословенное слово!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bring us together, blessed word!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>rajsom adæm æmbyrd kænyn bajdydtoj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>утром народ стал собираться</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>in the morning people began to gather</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æræmbyrdysty Nart xæznatæ warynmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>собрались Нарты делить сокровища</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Narts gathered together to share treasures</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 16</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Nartæ cælxæmbyrdæj badtysty k˳yvdy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Нарты, собравшись кругом, сидели на пиру</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Narts gathered in a circle sat at the feast</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>dæ æmbyrd cæmæn xalys?</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зачем ты прерываешь твое собрание?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>why are you interrupting your meeting?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>73</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Nartæ īnnæ bon æræmbyrd sty Wyryzmægmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Нарты на другой день собрались у Урузмага</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Narts gathered the next day at Uruzmag's place</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>72 - 73</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>binʒitæ... ratæxioncæ sæxecæn zumægmæ mud æmburd kænunmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>пчелы вылетают собирать себе на зиму мед</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bees fly out to collect honey for the winter</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 96</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>adæm dʼalvars æmbyrd sty</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>народ окружает тебя</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>the people are crowding</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Лука"/><biblScope>8 45</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>cæmæn wæ æmbyrd kæny Qævdyn?</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>зачем вас собирает Кавдын?</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>why is Qavdyn convoking you?</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>īwmæ næ rambyrd kæn, arfæjy ʒyrd!</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>собери нас вместе, благословенное слово!</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bring us together, blessed word!</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>39</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>rajsom adæm æmbyrd kænyn bajdydtoj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>утром народ стал собираться</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>in the morning people began to gather</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>æræmbyrdysty Nart xæznatæ warynmæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>собрались Нарты делить сокровища</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Narts gathered together to share treasures</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III 16</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>Nartæ cælxæmbyrdæj badtysty k˳yvdy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Нарты, собравшись кругом, сидели на пиру</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Narts gathered in a circle sat at the feast</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*hām-bṛ-ta-</w></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>haṃbar- ‘</w> <gloss><q>составлять</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>haṃbirsta</w> <gloss><q>соединенный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ham-bərətī-</w> <gloss><q>собирание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>sambhṛti-</w> <gloss><q>приготовление</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>сборы</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>со-бирать</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>со-брание</w></mentioned>, . Ос. форма предполагает %iham-bṛta-%i, а не %iham-bṛti-%i, так как в последнем случае мы имели бы %i*æmbyrc%i или %i*æmbylc%i (cp., например, %ixælc%i из %i*xvarti%i и др.). Корень %ibhṛ-%i, %ibher-%i, %ibhur-%i ‘двигаться’ и пр. широко представлен в индоевропейских языках (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 157, 167 сл., 191</biblScope></bibl>).* Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_læbūryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byrun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byrdæn"/>.%n<bibl/>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*hām-bṛ-ta-</w></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/> <w>haṃbar- ‘</w> <gloss><q>make up</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>haṃbirsta</w> <gloss><q>connected</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>ham-bərətī-</w> <gloss><q>gathering</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>sambhṛti-</w> <gloss><q>preparation</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>gathering</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <w>со-бирать</w> <gloss><q>collect</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>со-брание</w> <gloss><q>collection</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Ossetic form implies %iham-bṛta-%i but not %iham-bṛti-%i, since in the latter case e would have had %i*æmbyrc%i or %i*æmbylc%i (cf, for instance, %ixælc%i from %i*xvarti%i etc.). The root %ibhṛ-%i, %ibher-%i, %ibhur-%i ‘move’ etc. шis widespread in Indo-European languages (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 157, 167 сл., 191</biblScope></bibl>).* Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_læbūryn"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byrun"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_byrdæn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>19</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>